content:
Manage the Data Source for an Experience Component

Some Experience components use data sources to pull in information to display. If your experience component doesn't have or doesn't need a data source, you can skip this topic.

Most data sources used by experience components are one of these:

Integration Procedure

Omnistudio Data Mapper

Apex Remote used for a Vlocity Insurance service

Determine what data source you plan to use. If using a Vlocity Insurance service or out-of-the-box Data Mappers or Integration Procedures, determine remote options and settings. If custom, ensure it's created and tested.

Replace the Data Source on the FlexCard
Modify Options and Inputs on the Data Source
Make Changes to the Data Source Directly

Customize a Component

If you need to replace the data source, modify options, or make direct changes to the data source.
title: Customizing Insurance Experience Components
